      <intermediateExchange id="f761e520-285e-536e-b563-5020e68bc510" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="1333-74-0" amount="0.0020471334817801557" intermediateExchangeId="8d78a0dc-1489-48c1-8bc4-7c120f318216" activityLinkId="4883952d-00a3-5cc5-aeb4-3a7505511862">
        <name xml:lang="en">hydrogen, gaseous, medium pressure, merchant</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
2.01588g/mol is the molar mass of hydrogen, liquid (H2). 
118.08924g/mol is the molar mass of succinic acid (C4H6O4). 

Succinic acid is produced through hydrogenation of maleic acid [CAS number :  108-31-6]. Nickel is used as catalyst.  The nickel  catalyst in not consider significant in terms of emissions for the reaction and it is therefore onlz included in the input side. 
Chemical reaction : C4H2O3 + H2O + H2 --&gt; C4H6O4 . A process efficiency of 95% is assumed. </comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.0020471334817801557" mu="-6.191314765938416" variance="0.0006" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.010025"/>
